summary: I am feeling so torn because... I like Gendrya. I always have (first when they became friends in S2 and now something more in...
body:
I am feeling so torn because…

I like Gendrya. I always have (first when they became friends in S2 and now something more in S8). I was even surprised at myself how much I cared about them after they reunited. So, Arya rejecting him was sad. But, on the other hand…

I also liked that she did. Can you really see her as a Lady of Storm’s End? When I think of Arya and Gendry, I like to think of them living a bit like the free folk. We don’t kneel. Fuck the king. The Hound would be proud. You know, that sort of thing. And more than anything I would like to see - not just in fiction, IRL too - women choosing to be on their own. And out of all the female characters on GOT, Arya is the most likely one to do so. Maybe Brienne too, though with her heart being broken now, it would be too tragic (I still think she will get together with Tormund at the end). 

Of course, it’s easy to write about a woman leaving some douchebag behind and be happy by herself. But what if it’s not a douchebag she leaves behind, what if it’s a great guy like Gendry? That’s some challenge for a writer! (Not GOT writer, I mean generally, because I’m starting to ramble.)

Anyway, these two are probably not over. Like I said in a previous post, it was Daenerys who granted Gendry Storm’s End and Daenerys may well not end up as the queen anyway, so he will not get Storm’s End. Or he’ll say no thanks to whoever will take the throne at the end. Bronn should get it then, lol.

So that’s my thoughts.

summary: Game of thrones is NOT that shocking in killing characters
title: Game of thrones is NOT that shocking in killing characters
body:
I was talking with my daughter (yes, all my paswords are her nickname, very safe, I know, promised change that) and we have a conclusion that actually Game of Thrones is not very shocking in killing particular characters. If you know some rules, of course.

1. They already knew that show would be many seasons so first you must killed the older character to make younger to develop - Robert Baratheon, Ned Stark, Catelyn Stark, Tywin Lannister

2. Then you killing character more safe in your fictional world to make your character more powerful - Khal Drogo died to make Daenerys strong, Robb died to make Jon the leader, Margaery died to make Sansa better in playing games, Waif died to make Arya the best assassin. Still not sure about Rickon and Shireen, for now it looks like they make a room for new lords (like Bran and Gendry or like my daughter claimed only Gendry, she thinks that Gendry ultimately take Arya’s name and she will be Wardress of North and Sansa President of Kingdoms Council but for me that idea is ridiculous)

3. Also during the show you killing less important villains - Viserys, Joffrey, Ramsey, High Sparrow, Second Sons, Littlefinger and, you still have hard time to believe it, Night King. Because the main villain of Game of Thrones is Lannisters TRIO! Yes, also Tyrion. He survived all these time not to redeem himself (because, let’s be honest he wasn’t that bad like his siblings) but ultimately occur to be as bas as them. That’s why Oberyn must died - Tyrion with his siblings looks like one of the good guys, without them he could be corrupted.

BTW I love Dorne plot. It looks like D&D made Oberyn great entrance, then asked Martin ,,And how Dorne would be part of great finale?”,,Hmm, actually almost none”. ,,Ok, David let’s kill them all”

4. And the final part - killing characters with none role in GREAT FINALE. Dorne - kill them all, Tyrells - kill them all, Baratheon - kill them all (well, except for Gendry but he couldn’t be that important if any of them would be alive), Frey - kill them all, Vale - Robin is still alive?! What about Edmure Tully?

So that’s all about shocking deaths but I little worried because Martin don’t like Battlestar Galactica ending and in my opinion is really good, bittersweet ending and I have no idea what he could imagine as bittersweet ….

He survived all these time not to redeem himself (because, let’s be honest he wasn’t that bad like his siblings) but ultimately occur to be as bas as them. That’s why Oberyn must died - Tyrion with his siblings looks like one of the good guys, without them he could be corrupted.

What about Edmure Tully?

So that’s all about shocking deaths but I little worried because Martin don’t like Battlestar Galactica ending and in my opinion is really good, bittersweet ending and I have no idea what he could imagine as bittersweet ….

summary:
" It's just a stupid sword," she said, aloud this time...
... but it wasn't.
Needle was Robb and Bran and Rickon, her mother and...
body:
“ It’s just a stupid sword,” she said, aloud this time…

… but it wasn’t.

Needle was Robb and Bran and Rickon, her mother and her father, even Sansa. Needle was Winterfell’s grey walls, and the laughter of its people. Needle was the summer snows, Old Nan’s stories, the heart tree with its red leaves and scary face, the warm earthy smell of the glass gardens, the sound of the north wind rattling the shutters of her room. Needle was Jon Snow’s smile.

— Arya Stark, A Feast for Crows.

~ oh, my feelings…..

summary: Sansa is not getting any consequences for putting Dany's life in danger in the next episodes, I'm calling it. She is D&D's...
question: Sansa is not getting any consequences for putting Dany's life in danger in the next episodes, I'm calling it. She is D&D's Creator's Pet. She will just get her pretty castle to keep scheming without any living soul questioning her decisions.
answer:
100% agreed. In the last few seasons Sansa has basically gotten a blank check to do whatever she wants and, no matter how many times she puts her own desires before her own family, no matter who she manipulates or how unjustified her behavious is, the writers don’t really make her deal with the consequences of her actions. She just keeps going, not changing at all because she has no motivation to change.

Jon shouldn’t have said she was right after she hid the army of the Vale before the BotB, the Vale lords should have demanded some actual proof of LF’s betrayals before they allowed him to be executed, someone should have told her how stupid it is to openly dismiss Daenerys when she comes to help. Missandei deserved a medal for pointing out that Dany and her armies were the only reason her precious North had a chance against the army of the dead.

Jon should find out Sansa betrayed his secret the very same day he told her and this time he should not forgive her. Sansa used his parentage to hurt the woman he loves right after she saved the North. After Sansa swore she would never tell anyone. Arya should find out and be as pissed as she was in season 7 when she thought Sansa would betray Jon, because that’s what she has done. Sadly Bran doesn’t have any  reactions anymore, but if he were still Bran and not the 3ER he would be upset with Sansa too.

She should lose the respect of the northen lords and the northeners for being an oathbreaker, for using Jon as pawn. She should lose the power she loves so much. 

But honestly I don’t think the show will go there. I think she will get one of the best endings, regardless of her actions.
